
APPY FIZZ
Appy Fizz is a product by Parle Agro, introduced in India in 2005. Appy Fizz consists of carbonated apple juice, and can be used as the basis for cocktails. After the success of Appy which was clean apple juice, Parle launched its sequel product as Grappo Fizz, which is a carbonated grape juice.
The drink was the subject of a failed campaign of advertising at cricket matches in 2005-08.
Appy Fizz is also manufactured and marketed in Bangladesh by Global Beverage Co Ltd. under licence from Parle Agro.
